Dons Earn Fourth Straight Win, Sweep Redhawks in Three Sets
The University of San Francisco volleyball team achieved its fourth consecutive win by sweeping Seattle U 3-0. The Dons faced a tough first set but rallied to secure a 26-24 victory, followed by wins of 25-19 and 25-23 in the subsequent sets. Emilija Arsic led the attack with 15 kills and a .429 hitting percentage, while the team maintained a solid .298 hitting percentage overall, marking their third straight match above .250.
- San Francisco recorded a .298 hitting percentage in the match.
- Emilija Arsic contributed a team-high 15 kills with a hitting percentage of .429.
- The Dons improved their season record to 7-20, with a conference record of 5-12.
- Sweeping over Seattle U, the Dons demonstrated strong offensive and defensive synergy throughout the match.
The Dons will conclude their 2025 season at home against Washington State on Saturday, Nov. 29, as they aim to finish on a winning note.
Bottom LineSan Francisco's steady performance and teamwork are key factors in their recent wins, reinvigorating hopes for a strong finish to the season. Keeping up this momentum will be essential as they face their final match against Washington State.
